               <p>MR. BOLLAND conducted the prosecution.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-212-person1886">
                  WILLIAM 
                  OXLEY
               <interp inst="t18270913-212-person1886" type="surname" value="OXLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-212-person1886" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-212-person1886" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable of St. Martin in the Fields. On the morning of the 27th of July, in consequence of information, I went to <placeName id="t18270913-212-crimeloc1198">Scotland-yard</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-212-crimeloc1198" type="placeName" value="Scotland-yard"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-212-crimeloc1198" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-212-off1192 t18270913-212-crimeloc1198"></join>, at five o'clock, with Lemon - I saw the three prisoners digging there; no other person was near them - I waited about three quarters of an hour, and saw them take a large piece of pipe out of the earth - open the trap-door of a dung hole, and put it in there; they then took two or three shorter pieces, and put them there - they worked on till eight o'clock. I then saw Collins and William Murphy take it up, chop it into pieces, and put it into a barrow, which Collins wheeled down Parliament-street; William Murphy ran and joined him in Parliament-street (Dennis Murphy remained at work). I followed them to Schofield's, in Dean's-yard - I saw them take the lead out and carry it into the shop; I immediately went in, seized William Murphy, and told Schofield it was stolen goods; here is the lead, it is pieces of large pipes.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. William Murphy and Collins took it away? A. Yes; but Dennis came to the very spot where they were taken, in about ten minutes - eight o'clock is the time they leave work; they were working at the office of the Board of Works, Scotland-Yard.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-212-person1887">
                  WILLIAM 
                  LEMON
               <interp inst="t18270913-212-person1887" type="surname" value="LEMON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-212-person1887" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-212-person1887" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. Oxley's account is correct; I saw them take the lead and put it into the dunghole - I followed William Murphy and Collins to Schofield's; Dennis came there afterwards and was taken.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-212-person1888">
                  WILLIAM 
                  SCHOFIELD
               <interp inst="t18270913-212-person1888" type="surname" value="SCHOFIELD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-212-person1888" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-212-person1888" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a plumber and live in Dean's-yard. On the night of the 26th of July, William Murphy came to my house, and asked if I would buy any lead; he said there was some which laid near the surface of the ground, and the people had given it them; I said he might let me see it; next morning William Murphy brought it into my shop - I did not notice Collins near.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-212-person1889">
                  EDWARD 
                  CROCKER
               <interp inst="t18270913-212-person1889" type="surname" value="CROCKER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-212-person1889" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-212-person1889" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a labourer in trust, under the Board of Works. I received information, went to this spot, and missed this lead - it is an old service pipe, which came from the mews, and served the reservoir; it is the property of the Crown - I have not compared it, but it is<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182709130110"></xptr>missing from the place, and this appears to be the same; I suppose it has been down two hundred years, it is worth about 16s.; it is remarkably thick.</p>
               <p>COLLINS - <rs id="t18270913-212-verdict1199" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270913-212-verdict1199" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 23.</p>
               <p>WILLIAM MURPHY - <rs id="t18270913-212-verdict1200" type="verdictDescription">
